=== North America ===

In Canada, Bell Mobility[tpl]cite web|url=http://www.bell.ca/Mobility/Products/Galaxy_Nexus|title=Galaxy Nexus page|work=Cell phone carrier product page|publisher=Bell Mobility[/tpl] and Virgin Mobile launched the device on December 8, 2011 for C$649 with a cancelable contract.  Vidéotron announced a January 13, 2012 release, but the smartphone's release was delayed to February 8, 2012.Major Canadian Carriers Announce Impending Availability of Galaxy Nexus. Androidpolice.com (2011-11-15). Retrieved on 2011-11-21.  Telus began selling the phone for C$649 on January 13, 2012, while Fido and Rogers Wireless began selling the phone on the 13th in limited quantities for C$600 ($585) no strings attached. On February 3, 2012 Wind Mobile began selling the phone for C$599.
The LTE version of the Galaxy Nexus was launched in the United States on December 15, 2011 through Verizon Wireless for a subsidized price of $299.99 with a new two-year customer agreement.[tpl]cite web|last= Nickinson |first= Phil |title= Available from Verizon December 15 ... The Samsung Galaxy Nexus!!! |url= http://www.androidcentral.com/official-verizon-galaxy-nexus-availability-announcment |publisher= AndroidCentral |accessdate= 14 December 2011 [/tpl]  There were rumors that Verizon had confirmed the device was to be launched on December 9, along with the ability to preorder the Motorola Droid XYBoard (Xoom 2). That date, however, came and went without a product release. On April 24, 2012,[tpl]cite web|last= Joire |first= Myriam |title= Google back in the smartphone sales game: unlocked Galaxy Nexus HSPA+ (GSM) available for $399 |url= http://www.engadget.com/2012/04/24/google-galaxy-nexus-unlocked-on-sale-gsm-hspa/ |publisher= Engadget |accessdate= 4 May 2012 [/tpl] a GSM/UMTS, SIM-unlocked version was officially released in the United States by Google in the Play Store for $399. It works on both AT&T's and T-Mobile's networks, as well as [tpl]Reference necessary|over 200 other networks[tpl]Which?|date=May 2012[/tpl] worldwide.|date=May 2012[/tpl] Sprint officially announced the Galaxy Nexus for their network at CES 2012, and was released on April 22, 2012. It was released as one of Sprint Nextel's first LTE smartphones.[tpl]cite news| url= http://www.forbes.com/sites/mobiledia/2012/01/10/ces-2012-sprint-ramps-up-4g-with-galaxy-nexus-lte-devices/ |work= Forbes [/tpl][tpl]cite web|url= http://techcrunch.com/2012/01/09/sprint-unveils-first-lte-phones-the-galaxy-nexus-and-the-lg-viper/ |title= Sprint Unveils First LTE Phones: The Galaxy Nexus And The LG Viper |publisher= TechCrunch |date= 2012-01-09 |accessdate= 2012-02-20 [/tpl][tpl]cite web|url= http://www.engadget.com/2012/01/10/sprint-galaxy-nexus-lte-smartphone-unveiled-engadget-stage-ces-2012/ |title= Sprint's Galaxy Nexus shown on Engadget's CES stage by David Owens! |publisher= Engadget |date= |accessdate= 2012-02-20 [/tpl][tpl]cite web|last= Dolcourt |first= Jessica |url= http://news.cnet.com/8301-17938_105-57356231-1/sprints-samsung-galaxy-nexus-sweeter-with-google-wallet-hands-on/ |title= Sprint's Samsung Galaxy Nexus sweeter with Google Wallet (hands-on) | Crave - CNET |publisher= News.cnet.com |date= 2012-01-10 |accessdate= 2012-02-20 [/tpl][tpl]cite web|url= http://www.engadget.com/2012/01/10/sprint-galaxy-nexus-lte-smartphone-unveiled-engadget-stage-ces-2012/ |title= Sprint confirms Galaxy Nexus release date: coming April 22nd for $200, preorders open now |publisher= Engadget |date= |accessdate= 2012-02-21 [/tpl]
In Mexico, the Galaxy Nexus was officially announced to the media on March 8, 2012 in an exclusive launch event held in Mexico City. It was officially released to sales to registered buyers on March 15, 2012 by means of a "night-only sale" at some qualified Telcel Customer Attention Centers (CAC) and the day after: March 16, it went into general availability. Pre-registration to qualify for the night-only sale was required by visiting www.galaxynexus.com.mx.  On March 13, 2012, the registration (sign-up) numbers and phones assigned to the discount promotion were already sold-out. thumb|left|100px|Samsung Galaxy Nexus - Mexico's TELCEL SIM locked - SIM Unlock code request screen
Those who got a registration number on the promotion web site were entitled to attend the night-sale on Telcel qualifying Customer Attention Centers (CAC) during 16, 17, or 18 March, to the CAC of their choosing. After those dates, the Galaxy Nexus started selling at its regular list price for Mexico either on a pre-paid plan or, on post-paid plans with some operator subsidy.
The Galaxy Nexus, for the time being, will be available exclusively with Telcel at a price of approximately MXN$10,500 pesos. on a pre-paid plan basis. Substantial discounts for the phone will be available for previous customers with a post-payment (monthly billing) plan and to those who buy post-payment plans.[tpl]cite web|last=Onofre|first=Julio|title=Llega a México el Galaxy Nexus de Samsung|url=http://eleconomista.com.mx/tecnociencia/2012/03/08/llega-mexico-verdugo-iphone-galaxy-nexus|publisher=El Economista|accessdate=10 March 2012[/tpl]  The Galaxy Nexus in Mexico is being sold SIM locked to TELCEL. 
There are some builds of Android 4.0 (Ice Cream Sandwich) that are controlled by Google and some that are controlled by Samsung. While the Verizon version includes two preinstalled carrier apps, atypical of Nexus phones, it still comes with an unlockable boot loader, and therefore it is still easy to root the device.[tpl]cite web|last=Cipriani |first=Jason |url=http://howto.cnet.com/8301-11310_39-57352473-285/how-to-easily-root-your-galaxy-nexus/ |title=How to easily root your Galaxy Nexus | How To - CNET |publisher=Howto.cnet.com |date=2011-11-30 |accessdate=2012-01-07[/tpl][tpl]cite web|url=http://www.androidcentral.com/verizon-galaxy-nexus-root-toolkit-makes-process-easier-ever |title=Verizon Galaxy Nexus root toolkit makes the process easier than ever |publisher=Android Central |date= |accessdate=2012-01-07[/tpl] The Verizon version blocks Google Wallet,[tpl]cite web|last=Musil |first=Steven |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1035_3-57337210-94/verizon-blocks-google-wallet-on-galaxy-nexus/ |title=Verizon blocks Google Wallet on Galaxy Nexus | Mobile - CNET News |publisher=News.cnet.com |date=2011-12-05 |accessdate=2012-02-20[/tpl][tpl]cite news| url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052970204770404577081610232043208.html | work=The Wall Street Journal | first1=Amir | last1=Efrati | first2=Anton | last2=Troianovski | title=War Over the Digital Wallet | date=2011-12-07[/tpl][tpl]cite news| url=http://money.cnn.com/2011/12/06/technology/verizon_blocks_google_wallet/index.htm | work=CNN | title=Verizon blocks Google Wallet | date=2011-12-06[/tpl] however, users at xda-developers managed to create a modified APK of Google Wallet installable on those phones.[tpl]cite web|url=http://www.xda-developers.com/android/easily-install-google-wallet-onto-galaxy-nexus-with-an-apk/ |title=Easily Install Google Wallet onto Galaxy Nexus with an APK |publisher=xda-developers |date=2011-12-18 |accessdate=2012-02-20[/tpl][tpl]cite web|last=Newman |first=Jared |url=http://www.pcworl